<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-09-0586 </DOCNO><TEXT>Powerful micro based systems which can support major statistical database packages are now becoming readily available. With this expansionthe problem of providing technical support is also becoming acute. Expertsystems techniques suggest themselves as a means of delivering this expertise.This position paper considers the available paradigms and their relationshipto the needs of packages which support clinical follow-up studies. Inthe process several problems in the resulting man-machine interfacesare identified as areas for further study. These problems are of moregeneral interest than the medical area which motivated this study.</TEXT></DOC>